abstract_ssm: Records of the Wednesday Club, a Manhattan-based women's group organized in 1920 to discuss current events, topics of interest, and books of the day, at Wednesday afternoon meetings held between November and May. Includes by-laws, minutes, annual reports, membership lists, programs, some correspondence, and financial accounts.
